The paper presents an approach for synthesizing reactive robot motion plans, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach is based on compilation to Syntax-Guided Synthesis (SyGuS) specifications, which involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of SyGuS formalism to solve a bounded two-player reachability game, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and formal methods (cs.SY).
